263
00:26:55,416 --> 00:26:59,305
I hope you won’t let me down.

264
00:27:00,485 --> 00:27:02,404
Even if you don’t love God,

265
00:27:03,085 --> 00:27:05,300
He still loves you.

266
00:27:06,112 --> 00:27:10,909
The fact that you’re here right now
is already His mercy.

267
00:27:12,875 --> 00:27:17,307
And you know very well
what scholarship you received.

268
00:27:20,355 --> 00:27:22,300
A diocesan scholarship.

269
00:27:24,432 --> 00:27:29,005
Your duty isn’t only to study.

270
00:27:31,027 --> 00:27:32,907
While you’re here,

271
00:27:33,343 --> 00:27:38,085
I want you to find yourself
and see how you can serve God.

272
00:27:39,742 --> 00:27:42,401
But if you keep behaving like this,

273
00:27:43,761 --> 00:27:46,345
I’ll have to ask you to leave the school.

274
00:27:51,330 --> 00:27:52,330
Yes.

275
00:28:01,195 --> 00:28:04,355
Master Phak asked me to bring you
these documents to sign, Father.

276
00:28:05,519 --> 00:28:06,519
Thank you.

277
00:28:06,555 --> 00:28:07,555
You're welcome.

278
00:28:22,159 --> 00:28:24,945
Tanrak, do you know what the painting
Ticket to Heaven means?

279
00:28:29,706 --> 00:28:33,205
It tells the story of the path to heaven.

280
00:28:34,235 --> 00:28:39,703
Along the way, beasts devour sinful humans

281
00:28:41,422 --> 00:28:43,305
and tempt people off the path.

282
00:28:49,699 --> 00:28:51,604
I’m leaving Barth in your care.

283
00:28:52,313 --> 00:28:54,404
He needs help right now.

284
00:28:55,186 --> 00:28:58,906
And I believe you can help him.

285
00:29:01,015 --> 00:29:02,015
Yes, Father.

286
00:30:42,105 --> 00:30:44,506
Hey, Tanrak,
what are you standing around for?

287
00:30:44,735 --> 00:30:47,307
Hurry up. I need to take a dump,
or we’ll be late for class.

288
00:30:55,707 --> 00:30:57,204
Students, salute.

289
00:30:59,293 --> 00:31:00,404
Thank you, sir.

290
00:31:03,055 --> 00:31:07,601
Hey, Master Phak wants us to help
the younger kids on duty this evening.

291
00:31:07,937 --> 00:31:11,302
They just assigned duties,
and they’re still kind of confused.

292
00:31:11,869 --> 00:31:12,869
Sure.

293
00:31:13,515 --> 00:31:15,405
They’re probably
as lost as you were in Grade 7.

294
00:31:15,855 --> 00:31:16,855
When was I lost?

295
00:31:16,995 --> 00:31:19,155
When you wandered off
to the 60th Anniversary Building.

296
00:31:19,413 --> 00:31:20,584
What were you even doing there alone?

297
00:31:20,608 --> 00:31:22,605
Well, to meet you, apparently.

298
00:31:23,866 --> 00:31:26,306
Yeah, so we were both idiots.

299
00:32:05,905 --> 00:32:07,207
How do you spell your name?

300
00:32:09,309 --> 00:32:12,902
Bodin. B-O-D-I-N.

301
00:32:19,985 --> 00:32:20,985
And your nickname?

302
00:32:25,519 --> 00:32:27,607
Barth. B-A-R-T-H.

303
00:32:39,721 --> 00:32:43,035
Here. Sign in for homeroom roll call.

304
00:33:44,155 --> 00:33:47,605
Hey, aren’t we
supposed to play football today?

305
00:33:49,605 --> 00:33:50,605
I know.

306
00:33:51,815 --> 00:33:53,575
That's why I’m playing
basketball right here.

307
00:33:55,207 --> 00:33:56,702
Fine. Suit yourself.

308
00:33:59,502 --> 00:34:00,607
Damn.

309
00:34:02,765 --> 00:34:04,125
I even made the effort to ask him.

310
00:34:15,343 --> 00:34:17,404
Kong, Tanrak, wanna play football?

311
00:34:18,158 --> 00:34:19,158
We’re good.

312
00:34:19,752 --> 00:34:20,752
Okay.

313
00:34:34,885 --> 00:34:35,885
Hey, Kong.

314
00:34:36,865 --> 00:34:39,425
Now that you’re here at school,
who helps your mom with work?

315
00:34:40,362 --> 00:34:42,204
Everyone in my village knows each other.

316
00:34:42,505 --> 00:34:43,707
They all help out.

317
00:34:48,082 --> 00:34:51,808
Is everyone in your village Catholic?

318
00:34:54,027 --> 00:34:55,106
Yeah, pretty much.

319
00:35:00,902 --> 00:35:04,906
You know, when my mom found out
I got a scholarship here,

320
00:35:05,771 --> 00:35:07,204
she was over the moon.

321
00:35:14,478 --> 00:35:19,107
People like us don’t have many choices.

322
00:35:20,133 --> 00:35:23,309
Just having an ID card
and a place to study

323
00:35:24,931 --> 00:35:28,404
is probably the best choice
we could ask for.

324
00:35:34,965 --> 00:35:36,505
It’s the best choice for me too.

325
00:35:48,845 --> 00:35:50,306
They're actually pretty good.

326
00:36:01,795 --> 00:36:04,405
Go on.

327
00:36:04,735 --> 00:36:05,805
Run!

328
00:36:55,491 --> 00:36:57,300
Where the hell are my headphones?

329
00:36:58,192 --> 00:37:00,506
Hey, have you seen my headphones?

330
00:37:00,745 --> 00:37:01,745
You.

331
00:37:11,146 --> 00:37:12,503
Did you take my headphones?

332
00:37:14,002 --> 00:37:15,442
What the hell are you talking about?

333
00:37:16,465 --> 00:37:18,601
The headphones
you pulled out of my locker.

334
00:37:21,417 --> 00:37:22,709
I put everything over there.

335
00:37:23,229 --> 00:37:24,402
You took them yourself.

336
00:37:25,495 --> 00:37:27,007
Well, now they’re gone.

337
00:37:29,315 --> 00:37:31,107
What the hell does that
have to do with me?

338
00:37:31,263 --> 00:37:32,808
Hey, asshole, watch your mouth.

339
00:37:33,102 --> 00:37:34,605
I’m talking nicely to you.

340
00:37:34,811 --> 00:37:36,505
Are you messing with me? Huh?

341
00:37:37,425 --> 00:37:38,602
You don't wanna mess with me.

342
00:37:40,731 --> 00:37:43,355
I’ve been here forever,
and nothing ever went missing.

343
00:37:43,857 --> 00:37:45,906
Then you show up, and now my stuff’s gone.

344
00:37:46,324 --> 00:37:47,324
Asshole.

345
00:37:47,495 --> 00:37:48,939
Watch how you talk to me.

346
00:37:49,844 --> 00:37:51,641
What the hell does your stuff
have to do with me?

347
00:37:51,665 --> 00:37:53,707
- Oh, you wanna run your mouth?
- That's right.

348
00:37:53,855 --> 00:37:55,066
What the hell does that
have to do with me?

349
00:37:55,090 --> 00:37:56,290
You wanna run your mouth? Huh?

350
00:37:59,340 --> 00:38:01,605
Barth! Barth! Barth! Stop!

351
00:38:02,193 --> 00:38:02,730
Kongkit!

352
00:38:03,152 --> 00:38:04,302
Or you'll get expelled.

353
00:38:06,718 --> 00:38:09,503
If you don’t stop,
you’re both getting suspended.

354
00:38:11,985 --> 00:38:14,405
He accused me of stealing his stuff.
I didn’t steal anything.

355
00:38:14,445 --> 00:38:15,802
- He took my headphones!
- Hey!

356
00:38:16,815 --> 00:38:18,008
I said stop!

357
00:38:18,740 --> 00:38:21,900
Kongkit, who said you could use
headphones here?

358
00:38:26,785 --> 00:38:29,107
You, go. You too.

359
00:38:30,995 --> 00:38:32,602
Snapping at each other like dogs.

360
00:38:36,408 --> 00:38:38,082
Go. Everyone, break it up.

361
00:39:12,789 --> 00:39:14,505
Barth. What’s up?

362
00:39:14,785 --> 00:39:15,807
Looking for something?

363
00:39:16,835 --> 00:39:19,309
My desk’s been searched. My bag’s gone.

364
00:39:25,259 --> 00:39:26,306
Your bag?

365
00:39:27,785 --> 00:39:30,703
I saw… someone take it.

366
00:39:31,650 --> 00:39:32,650
Who?

367
00:39:34,084 --> 00:39:35,084
Who?

368
00:39:35,530 --> 00:39:36,530
Kongkit.

369
00:39:36,992 --> 00:39:37,992
Where did he go?

370
00:39:38,685 --> 00:39:40,205
He went toward the back of the school.

371
00:39:50,847 --> 00:39:51,847
Damn it.

372
00:40:11,865 --> 00:40:12,865
Kongkit!

373
00:40:16,595 --> 00:40:17,595
Kongkit!

374
00:40:22,035 --> 00:40:23,305
Where the hell is he?

375
00:40:25,235 --> 00:40:26,601
Kongkit, come out!

376
00:40:31,479 --> 00:40:32,479
Shit.

377
00:40:36,952 --> 00:40:38,607
Kongkit! Where are you, asshole?

378
00:40:40,213 --> 00:40:41,213
Come out!

379
00:40:48,155 --> 00:40:49,302
Shit.

380
00:41:08,029 --> 00:41:09,601
Shit! You went big, huh?

381
00:41:27,851 --> 00:41:28,851
Shit.

382
00:41:46,241 --> 00:41:49,602
Barth, what are you doing?

383
00:41:52,937 --> 00:41:53,937
Nothing.

384
00:42:02,137 --> 00:42:03,402
Want me to call Master?

385
00:42:08,235 --> 00:42:09,602
I said it’s nothing.

386
00:42:10,085 --> 00:42:11,503
Just go back. Stay out of it.

387
00:42:11,727 --> 00:42:12,727
I’ll handle it myself.

388
00:42:28,555 --> 00:42:29,808
I said, stay out of it.

389
00:42:32,709 --> 00:42:34,802
It’s okay. Let me help.

390
00:42:45,195 --> 00:42:46,795
Are you gonna run and tell Master again?

391
00:42:51,505 --> 00:42:54,081
Well, I wasn’t snitching.

392
00:42:55,055 --> 00:42:57,225
I just called him
to stop you guys from fighting.

393
00:43:04,774 --> 00:43:07,509
I thought you were gonna tell them
I stole Kongkit’s headphones.

394
00:43:12,601 --> 00:43:16,945
I know you didn’t steal them.

395
00:43:17,875 --> 00:43:21,204
During free time, I saw you
playing basketball the whole time.

396
00:43:23,095 --> 00:43:24,703
When would you have stolen them?

397
00:43:49,295 --> 00:43:51,408
No one believes someone like me anyway.

398
00:43:54,709 --> 00:43:55,709
Hey.

399
00:43:57,425 --> 00:44:02,082
What’s right is always right,
no matter who says it.

400
00:44:05,547 --> 00:44:07,755
Go preach somewhere else. I’m not two.

401
00:44:17,865 --> 00:44:18,865
Shit!

402
00:44:24,296 --> 00:44:25,703
Damn it, Kongkit!

403
00:44:33,075 --> 00:44:34,204
How is it, Barth?

404
00:44:37,265 --> 00:44:39,703
There’s no other way out.
Everything’s locked.

405
00:44:43,279 --> 00:44:45,604
Then stay here with me tonight.

406
00:44:46,201 --> 00:44:47,802
Someone will probably find us.

407
00:44:49,967 --> 00:44:50,967
When?

408
00:44:52,453 --> 00:44:53,453
Morning, I guess.

409
00:45:00,365 --> 00:45:04,305
If Master Phak checks
and we’re both missing,

410
00:45:04,759 --> 00:45:05,759
we’re so dead.

411
00:45:07,937 --> 00:45:10,905
I’ll tell Master I got stuck here
and you came to help me.

412
00:45:11,135 --> 00:45:12,295
You didn't do anything wrong.

413
00:45:17,085 --> 00:45:18,204
Relax.

414
00:45:19,365 --> 00:45:21,565
A good kid like you?
Everyone believes whatever you say.

415
00:45:22,227 --> 00:45:24,902
Me? Who knows what they’ll do to me.

416
00:45:30,435 --> 00:45:33,500
You didn’t do anything wrong.
I can back you up.

417
00:45:36,457 --> 00:45:37,706
Let’s hope that’s true.

418
00:45:41,617 --> 00:45:43,804
We should find somewhere to sleep.

419
00:45:43,910 --> 00:45:45,404
No one’s finding us now.

420
00:45:53,050 --> 00:45:57,715
What’s right is always right,
no matter who says it.

421
00:46:00,918 --> 00:46:02,675
Let’s see if what you said is true.

422
00:46:04,008 --> 00:46:05,608
You really love talking back, don't you?

423
00:46:16,771 --> 00:46:18,102
Are you sleeping here?

424
00:46:20,465 --> 00:46:23,106
Don’t. There's a lot of bat poop up there.

425
00:46:28,165 --> 00:46:29,202
Are you asleep yet?

426
00:46:31,174 --> 00:46:32,174
Yes.

427
00:46:35,462 --> 00:46:38,408
Why do you think this pool was abandoned?

428
00:46:42,090 --> 00:46:43,705
I said I’m asleep.

429
00:46:45,985 --> 00:46:47,404
Then how are you answering me?

430
00:47:10,294 --> 00:47:11,401
You really wanna know?

431
00:47:12,888 --> 00:47:15,509
I don’t think you do.

432
00:47:20,266 --> 00:47:21,703
Are you trying to scare me?

433
00:47:30,906 --> 00:47:32,076
You asked for it.

434
00:47:35,105 --> 00:47:43,105
This place used to be where…

435
00:47:46,878 --> 00:47:48,208
they would use…

436
00:47:51,075 --> 00:47:51,735
See that mark?

437
00:47:51,756 --> 00:47:52,756
Hey!

438
00:47:55,425 --> 00:47:57,001
You can tell me tomorrow.

439
00:48:06,481 --> 00:48:07,507
Don’t be scared.

440
00:48:08,936 --> 00:48:10,355
God is protecting us.

441
00:48:16,583 --> 00:48:18,155
You believe in ghosts too?

442
00:48:20,284 --> 00:48:21,284
No.

443
00:48:22,205 --> 00:48:23,604
When people die,

444
00:48:24,347 --> 00:48:27,804
they either go to heaven
or wait for judgment.

445
00:48:36,395 --> 00:48:37,395
Tanrak.

446
00:48:40,225 --> 00:48:41,506
I’m seriously asking you.

447
00:48:44,453 --> 00:48:46,265
Do you really believe in God?

448
00:48:53,076 --> 00:48:57,705
Like, do you truly believe…
wholeheartedly?

449
00:49:05,855 --> 00:49:07,502
I believe God is real.

450
00:49:09,902 --> 00:49:15,305
I believe my parents are with Him…

451
00:49:19,930 --> 00:49:21,002
up there.

452
00:49:30,015 --> 00:49:31,401
You really believe that?

453
00:49:35,315 --> 00:49:36,859
If you have enough faith,

454
00:49:38,396 --> 00:49:40,204
you’ll feel His presence yourself.

455
00:50:03,659 --> 00:50:04,659
You know what?

456
00:50:08,445 --> 00:50:10,207
I used to believe that too.

457
00:50:12,765 --> 00:50:13,765
And then…?

458
00:50:26,085 --> 00:50:28,005
Then one day, I realized

459
00:50:30,694 --> 00:50:34,906
your God never helped me at all.

460
00:50:46,746 --> 00:50:50,909
Maybe my God isn’t as kind as yours.

461
00:51:03,244 --> 00:51:04,604
Why do you think that?

462
00:51:13,507 --> 00:51:14,507
Forget it.

463
00:51:16,635 --> 00:51:18,700
I stopped thinking about God
a long time ago.

464
00:51:45,866 --> 00:51:47,004
Hey, come look at this.

465
00:51:48,525 --> 00:51:49,602
Master, over here!

466
00:51:59,485 --> 00:52:01,709
Hey, wake up.

467
00:52:46,815 --> 00:52:48,535
The only wrong thing you did
was to help me,

468
00:52:48,610 --> 00:52:49,795
and now you’re screwed too.

469
00:52:49,933 --> 00:52:52,909
I think you could’ve handled
this better, Tanrak.

470
00:52:52,995 --> 00:52:54,235
I’m really sorry, Father.

471
00:52:54,675 --> 00:52:55,902
Can I move over here?

472
00:52:56,244 --> 00:52:58,408
Father made me your buddy.

473
00:52:58,695 --> 00:52:59,801
So you should tutor me.

474
00:53:00,047 --> 00:53:01,275
Why should I tutor you?

475
00:53:01,595 --> 00:53:02,607
Because we’re friends.

476
00:53:02,815 --> 00:53:04,805
Since when are we friends? Huh?

477
00:53:07,051 --> 00:53:09,306
Since when are Tan and Barth besties?

478
00:53:09,407 --> 00:53:11,670
Yeah. When did they become close friends?

479
00:53:14,368 --> 00:53:16,103
Can you stop breaking the rules already?

480
00:53:17,202 --> 00:53:19,008
Come with me. I'll help you.

